# Fixtures and configs

## Suite fixtures (`data/<category>/<name>_v<n>.json`)

Validated through `SuiteDefinition` (see `src/spark_benchmark/suites.py`):

```json
{
  "name": "...",
  "category": "reliability | performance | quality | custom",
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "description": "...",
  "tasks": [
    {
      "task_id": "...",
      "prompt": "...",
      "context": "... or null",
      "reference": "... or null",
      "tags": ["..."],
      "metadata": { "expected_behavior": "..." }
    }
  ]
}
```

`metadata.expected_behavior` is the contract with the scorers — must be one of:

| Value | Suite | Scorer |
|---|---|---|
| `answer_from_context` | hallucination_grounding | reference / token-overlap match |
| `abstain` | hallucination_grounding | matches `ABSTAIN_PHRASES` |
| `correct_user` | hallucination_grounding | negation + reference present |
| `json_exact_match` | practical_structured_output | parsed JSON equals reference |
| `performance_probe` | openclaw_speed | every row counts as pass |
| `sustained_throughput_probe` | sustained_throughput | every row counts as pass |
| (humaneval / mbpp) | code_generation | requires `entry_point` + `tests` in metadata |

HumanEval / MBPP problems must keep canonical `task_id` (`humaneval/N`, `mbpp/N`)
so reference scores in `data/code/reference_scores.yaml` line up.

## Configs (`configs/`)

- `experiments/*.yaml` — `experiment.backend` must match a `configs/backends/<name>.yaml`; every name in `experiment.models` must have a matching `configs/models/<name>.yaml`.
- `models/*.yaml` — for `ollama` backend, `artifact_path` is the **Ollama tag** (e.g. `qwen3.6:35b`); for `llamacpp`, it's a path to a local **GGUF** file.
- `platforms/spark.yaml` — only Spark in v1.
- For Ollama-served models you can skip the YAML entirely; the TUI auto-detects them from `/api/tags` and synthesizes a `ModelConfig` (vision / embedding tags get greyed out, never benchmarked).

When adding a new model: pin sampling and aliasing in the NL parser
(`orchestration.parse_benchmark_request` — `alias_map`) so users can write the
short name in a sentence.
